/**
 * scene-router.js
 *
 * Bridges GPS zone changes (from gps-simulator.js) into audible scene
 * switches in the Pd patch running inside pd4web.
 *
 * Root cause fixed here:
 *   WebPatch/index.pd has no [r zone] receiver.  GPS zone floats sent by
 *   gps-simulator.js via window.Pd.sendFloat('zone', …) were silently
 *   discarded.  This module intercepts the 'gps-zone-change' CustomEvent,
 *   maps the pdZone number to a scene using the same 35-entry lookup table
 *   as alexandria_family_harness_router.pd, then applies the full scene
 *   parameter preset via individual sendFloat calls, wrapped in a
 *   master-fade transition so the switch is smooth.
 *
 * Zone → scene mapping source:
 *   Libs/alexandria_family_harness_router.pd  (#A set … line)
 *
 * Scene parameter data source:
 *   soundwalk_scene.pd  (all 45 scenes, each stored as receiver → value pairs)
 *
 * Fade mechanism:
 *   sceneMasterFade receiver in WebPatch/index.pd feeds a line~ through
 *   [pack f 2000] (changed from 120 ms → 2000 ms ramp).
 *   Sequence:  fadeOut(2 s) → 100 ms gap → applyParams → fadeIn(2 s).
 *
 * Exposed global: window.sceneRouter
 *   .applyScene(sceneNum)   – apply a named scene immediately (no fade)
 *   .goToZone(pdZone)       – full fade transition to zone's mapped scene
 */
